  "body": "As it stands, we currently have a 1 to 1 mapping from permission to rpc method. With the addition of multiple rpc methods that fall around the same action or permission, it is necessary for the `PermissionController` to be able to process a permission request for a `parent` permission and subsequently install the `child` permissions. This greatly reduces the visual overload you get from seeing multiple related permissions in the connect screen. \r\n\r\nThe first permission to have a group would be `snap_manageState` and then eventually the forthcoming custom ui rpc methods.",
